<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
        <title>Marko Custom Tags</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Marko Custom Tags</h1>
        <app-hello name="Frank"/>
        <app-hello-template name="John"/>
        <h2>
            The custom tags below come from the "sample-custom-tags-foo" package
            that is installed into this project:
        </h2>
        <sample-custom-tags-say-hello name="Jane"/>
        <sample-custom-tags-foo/>
        <h2>
            The custom tag below illustrates how to implement a tag that
            wraps content:
        </h2>
        <app-render-body classes=['foo', 'bar']>
          <p.baz>
            This <code>p</code> element will be included in the rendering.
            Notice that the <code>baz</code> class gets applied.
          </p>
        </app-render-body>
    </body>
</html>
